track_notes: Despite a gnarly bushwhack from Trail 37 up to the summit of Little Granite Mtn, both Litle Granite and Two Rock Mtn can be completed in a single day by an experienced hiker. This track shows only a hike to Little Granite Mtn from the trailhead off Iron Springs Rd at GPS 34.587955,-112.573744. Take Trail 37 north to a jumping off point at GPS 34.603075,-112.577109 to begin a bushwhack to the summit. You may find a barbed wire fence that intermittently runs most of the way to the summit. You can loosely follow the fenceline but it seems there is no way to avoid the thick brush and steep slope.
track_title: Little Granite Mountain via Trail 37 and Bushwhack

track_notes: This track follows the same routes as K9PM except it is a double.  I activated Little Granite first, the trail is nice but the bushwhack is a bit rough.  Sections are steep and slippery.  After coming down from the summit of Little Granite and returning to the trail, the remainder is relatively easy with a trail all the way up Two Rock.
track_title: Little Granite and Two Rock Mountains Double

track_notes: This track follows the same routes as K9PM except it is a double.  I activated Little Granite first, the trail is nice but the bushwhack is a bit rough. track_title: Little Granite and Two Rock Mountains Double
